<br>
So we're in the waiting room and I'm explaining to him, pulling no punches, that this is going to hurt and hurt bad...but it will only last for a second.  He has to get three shots, so trying to tell him to be a strong little man and it will all be over.<br>
<br>
So his turn is called, we go into the room, I sit him on my lap.  I hold one arm as the technician swabs the others.  I tell Terry to look at me and the tech gives the shot.  My kid screams &quot;OUCH! MEANIE!!!!&quot;  Well that wasn't too bad.  Two more to go, I tell him.  He says &quot;NO MORE!!!&quot; as the technician puts a bandaid on him.<br>
<br>
My kid starts staring at this bandaid as the tech says &quot;Ok, two more in the other arm and we are all done&quot;.<br>
<br>
Terry looks at the tech, looks at the bandaid, then rolls up his other sleeves and sticks out his arm.  Then, with the other hand, extends it and does the &quot;come here&quot; motion with his open/close fist and says (ala Rock) &quot;Just Bring It!&quot;<br>
<br>
We were laughing for 15 minutes, no joke.  Poor guy had to get another tech to give the other two shots because we couldn't stop laughing.<br>
<br>
Two more bandaids, three stickers, and one very strong little man.<br>
<br>
My kid is the coolest kid in town. <p><a href="http://www.yoursighost.com/members/Drackore" target="_blank">
