<br>
Now at first I thought the Air Force was my last hope of straightening me out.  After my dad died I just started chugging the booze like a fish.  I stopped eating, quit my civilian job, lost about 40lbs.  I was definately heading down.  Even in tech school I was spending my whole paycheck at the clubs.<br>
<br>
Graduated tech school, got married, got stationed in Montana (YEEEEE HAW).  Still drinking, rarely eating...then BAM.  Terry was born.<br>
<br>
It was funny.  I looked down, nothing but the big light shining.  Look up at my wife then looked down again and there he was (bloody mess).  However the light shining down on him would have made an excellent picture.<br>
<br>
Suddenly, without concentrated effort or thought...I grew up.  Who woulda thunk it???<br>
<br>
